## Database Reference

**Database name:** `polls_db`

**Description:** `polls_db` supports Pollify, a web-based polling application where users create and participate in public and private polls. It manages user authentication, poll creation, voting logic, and access control. A `permissions` field indicates the user role, granting access to admin tools when signed in.

---

### Tables

#### `users`
Stores user account details.

| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `user_id` | INT (PK) | Primary key; uniquely identifies each user |
| `username` | VARCHAR(50) | Username for login and display |
| `email` | VARCHAR(100) | User email address |
| `password_hash` | VARCHAR(255) | Hashed password for secure authentication |
| `created_at` | DATETIME | Timestamp of account creation |
| `last_login` | DATETIME | Timestamp of most recent login |
| `permissions` | INT | User role: `3` = admin, `2` = regular user |

#### `polls`
Stores individual polls and voting data.

| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `poll_id` | INT (PK) | Primary key; uniquely identifies each poll |
| `user_id` | INT (FK) | References poll creator; NULL for anonymous polls |
| `prompt` | TEXT | The poll question or statement |
| `option_a`, `option_b` | VARCHAR(255) | The two voting options |
| `a_count`, `b_count` | INT | Vote tallies for each option |
| `is_public` | BOOLEAN | Whether the poll is publicly accessible |
| `created_at` | DATETIME | Timestamp when the poll was created |
| `voter_ids` | TEXT | Stores voter IDs to prevent duplicate votes |

---

### Relationships

**`polls.user_id` → `users.user_id`**
One-to-many. A user can create multiple polls. If a user is deleted, all their polls are removed (`ON DELETE CASCADE`).
